SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1118
By McNally
A RESOLUTION to honor Michael Charles Webb of Monroe
County on the occasion of his retirement.
WHEREAS, Michael Charles Webb was born a citizen of the United States of America in
Ventura, California, and his parents relocated to Vonore when he was a youth; and
WHEREAS, Michael Charles Webb became known simply as "Mike Webb" locally as he
excelled to graduate from Vonore High School and later graduated from Tennessee Wesleyan
College with a Bachelor of Science degree in Business Management with a minor in
Economics/Business Administration in June 1986; and
WHEREAS, Mike Webb worked in financial and logistical production roles for the next
six years at Associates Financial Services, Sea Ray Boats, and Cobia Boat Company after his
college graduation; and
WHEREAS, on July 6, 1992, Mr. Webb became an employee of the Fort Loudon Electric
Cooperative (FLEC); his leadership and guidance have been instrumental in the various levels
of management in which he has served during his tenure with FLEC, having held the position of
Chief Financial Officer since 2011 and that of Assistant General Manager/Chief Financial Officer
since April 2014; and
WHEREAS, Mike Webb has always worked to be a contributor to the betterment of
several local and regional entities, including tenures as president of the Eastern District Power
Accountants Association, officer of the Southeast District Power Distributors Association, and
board member and current officer of the Tellico Reservoir Development Agency Board, a State-
authorized regional economic development agency; and
WHEREAS, he has rendered sterling service as a member of the Tennessee Electric
Cooperative Association's Accounting Planning Committee and currently serves as an officer of
SJR1118
017863
- 1 -

the Monroe County Economic and Community Development Committee and as a board
member of the Monroe County United Way; and
WHEREAS, during his thirty-four-year tenure as an employee of FLEC, Mr. Webb,
through his leadership and guidance, has proven instrumental in the cooperation among
Tennessee's utilities, as he acted to coordinate logistical needs, provide financial training and
oversight, navigate storm response assistance, and generally make sure the lights shined bright
the majority of his time on watch; and
WHEREAS, the region that FLEC serves has experienced tremendous change and
growth, due in part to his dedication to serving the area; when Mr. Webb started at FLEC in
1992, the Cooperative's electric plant was valued at $25,817,047 and served 18,887 members;
at the time of his retirement, the Cooperative's electric plant has grown to a value of over
$186,842,226 and serves 36,949 members, with over three decades of historical data to reflect
his working within balanced budgets while building the Cooperative's financial prowess to meet
the needs of the future; and
WHEREAS, Mike Webb has demonstrated an exemplary professional and personal
outlook by always maintaining a positive attitude through the trials encountered in the electric
utility industry; he has a volunteer spirit and exhibits leadership and commitment to creating a
better Tennessee; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby honor Michael Charles Webb on the
occasion of his retirement from Fort Loudon Electric Cooperative in May 2026, as we celebrate
his service and accomplishments, acknowledging the legacy he leaves by virtue of his
commitment and dedication.
- 2 - 017863

BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
